\f0\b \cf0 5. Ending the Stigma
\f1\b0 \
\

\f0\b Why Stigma Matters
\f1\b0 \
Misusing the term \'93OCD\'94 in casual conversation can lead to misunderstanding and minimize the struggles of those living with the disorder. Stereotypes and jokes may discourage individuals from seeking help or talking openly about their experiences.\
\

\f0\b Language Matters
\f1\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	\'95	Avoid: \'93I\'92m so OCD.\'94 \uc0\u8594  Instead: \'93I prefer things to be organized.\'94\
	\'95	Avoid: \'93Just stop thinking about it.\'94 \uc0\u8594  Instead: \'93I\'92m here if you want to talk.\'94\
\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf0 How We Can Create Change
\f1\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	\'95	Use respectful and informed language\
	\'95	Listen to real experiences of individuals with OCD\
	\'95	Stay educated about mental health\
	\'95	Choose words intentionally to promote understanding and empathy\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
